==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cadaveric
<hw>Ca*dav"er*ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of, pertaining
to, or resembling, a corpse, or the changes produced by death;
cadaverous; <as>as, <ex>cadaveric</ex> rigidity</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cadaveric alkaloid</b></col>, <cd>an alkaloid generated
by the processes of decomposition in dead animal bodies, and thought by
some to be the cause of the poisonous effects produced by the bodies.
See <er>Ptomaine</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cadaverin</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Cadaverine</ent>⟦br⟧
